-- Ford to invest $773 million across southeast Michigan
-- 
-- Thu Dec 27, 2012 12:28am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/12/27/us-ford-investment-idUSBRE8BQ01D20121227

 

 (Reuters) - Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) plans to invest more than $773 million on new equipment and capacity expansions across six manufacturing facilities in southeast Michigan in the United States. 
 The investment plan is part of its commitment to invest $6.2 billion in U.S. plants by 2015, the automaker said early on Thursday. (Reporting by  Sakthi Prasad  in Bangalore; Editing by  Daniel Magnowski )